{"key":"post-11323311","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11323311</id>\n<content>Nobody has ever &lt;i&gt;sterilized&lt;/i&gt; LC in the oven.&amp;nbsp; If they heated LC to 250F, it would have all boiled out and the jar would be dry.&amp;nbsp; Remember, mason jars don't hold pressure, only vacuum.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can sterilize dry verm or perlite in the oven, but not anything with moisture, such as grains or liquid culture.&amp;nbsp; This is why we use pressure cookers.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11323313</next>\n<prev>11323305</prev>\n<first>11323258</first>\n<last>11330231</last>\n<when>1256572957</when>\n<utime>10/26/09 07:02 PM</utime>\n</post>"}